    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fæzzæg" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>fæzzæg</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>осень</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>autumn</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>fæzzygon</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>autumn (adj.)</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>in autumn</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>fæzzygænd</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>озимь</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>winter crop</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>озимая вспашка</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>immature cones</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ærægvæzzæg</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>поздняя осень</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>late autumn</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>næ fæzzæg k˳ystæn ū</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>наша осень — (пора) работы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>out autumn is working time</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>fæzzæg ærcydīs</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>наступила осень</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>autumn came</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>17</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>kud ǧæzdug æj næ fæzzæg!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>как обильна наша осень!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>how abundant our autumn is!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>III 5</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Как и названия других времен года, — иранское слово (см. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_walʒæg"/> ‘весна’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_særd"/> ‘лето’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zymæg"/>
                    ‘зима’). Возводится к %i*pati-zyaka-%i, где %ipati%i — предлог со значением ‘к’,
                    а %izyaka%i — от %izyam%i ‘зима’: осень определяется как время года, когда дело
                    идет „к зиме“. Развитие формы: %i*pati-zyaka-%i → %i*fajzyak%i → %ifæzzæg%i
                    (%ipati%i → %ifaj%i, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fajnūst"/>; %ijz%i →
                    %izz%i, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazzajyn"/> из %ibajzajyn%i и др.).
                    Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>paīz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>pātez</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-pazend"><lang/>
                        <w>pādez</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>pij</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*patīz- (ptyz)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>paša</w>
                        <gloss><q>осень</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>13</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XII
                            329 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XII 329
                        ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Iranian word, like the names of other seasons (see <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_walʒæg"/> ‘spring’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_særd"/> ‘summer’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zymæg"/>
                    ‘winter’). It traces back to %i*pati-zyaka-%i, where %ipati%i is a preposition
                    with the meaning ‘to’, and %izyaka%i is from %izyam%i ‘winter’: autumn is
                    defined as the time of year when it is going on for winter. The form
                    development: %i*pati-zyaka-%i → %i*fajzyak%i → %ifæzzæg%i (%ipati%i → %ifaj%i,
                    as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fajnūst"/>; %ijz%i → %izz%i, as in <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_bazzajyn"/> from %ibajzajyn%i etc.). Cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>paīz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>pātez</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-pazend"><lang/>
                        <w>pādez</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/>
                        <w>pij</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*patīz- (ptyz)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>paša</w>
                        <gloss><q>autumn</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>13</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">XII 329
                        ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
